reviews.text: An excellent museum with very high quality displays produced by volunteers. Walking through the museum and looking at the displays you would think the entire place was laid out, designed and produced by professional museum designers. Well worth a visit. Especially if you live in Champaign County and haven't ever been there.

This place is a wealth of history! Between an old cattle scale, a grocery mart that's from the 1800's (inactive ) and a two story museum I am really surprised more people dont go here. A hidden gem right in front of everyone!

Nothing expansive or fancy here ... just a couple of rooms of exhibits. But what's there is very well-presented, and gives a nice overview of the history of the county. One room is dedicated to how WWII affected Champaign County, especially at the (now-defunct) Chanute Air Base in Rantoul. That was very interesting. The people that work/volunteer there are friendly and clearly knowledgeable. You could see it for free, but it's more than worth the $3 suggested donation. 
A very pleasant way to pass an hour.

It is a nice small museum. However, in April 2019, the overly eager security team still exists and severely damaged my overall experience. I did not feel free to discuss the art out loud with my partner, even though we were the only ones there besides staff. The constant eyes on made me feel rushed while viewing. At least if the staff is going to join us walking around they could be a giving an informal tour to make us feel a little at ease. It was just such an odd, uncomfortable experience. We discussed that instead of the art on the way home.

Great art pieces both up and downstairs. Very enjoyable place to visit with incoming guests and walking around campus. They were hosting a dance class on the day we stopped by with live music in one of the galleries.

Probably the best Museum in town. They showcase a lot of variety right from Egyptian/African civilizations to modern day Chicago art movements. If you have at least 10 people you can contact them and be a part of an organized tour which is amazing. They also have a coffee shop where you can meet and grab coffee before or after.

Love love love love love!  Stopped by with my stepdaughter to return tactile art -- they have an area where you are able to touch everything, experience it as it was used, to some degree, and you can even take pieces/prints elsewhere!  The permanent collection has LOVELY art nouveau pieces, but we didn't have time to go to most of the areas.
Great collection, wonderful events happen here. Plus there's a really good coffee shop in the museum. A must visit!

Beautiful theater for movies and shows. Really a jewel of Champaign located in downtown. 

Almost loose a star for lack of parking and metered spots.  

Wish some of the events were cheaper but they attract world class acts and you get what you pay for.

This is a specific review of Ebertfest at the Virginia. I attended to see a movie. It is supposed to be a film festival, but it is a self congratulatory party with no sense of film discovery or direction. The movie started 70, minutes late while the organizers and sponsors, including the University president, made the same fawning pontifications they do every year. I think the festival ran its course years ago, when Roger was still alive. Fully half of the movies are already available in the library.

Steady remodeling has reached a great plateau.  Really neat offerings at bargain prices.  Fun audiences!  Volunteer ushers delight full! Best ever! I attended movies there as a child, a teenager on dates,  married guy, and now senior citizen. 70 years!  Now the best!
Awesome old theater. Glad they restored it. Fun events held here like bad movie mondays.
Show was awesome! The theatre is old and beautiful. Loved the experience. Cheap concessions too

Love this theater. I love the FMG savings program, it saves me a fortune for our family of 3, it counts tickets and concessions. We went in this time and received a free large couples special - 2 large drinks and a large popcorn. The reserved seating is wonderful for me, I'm disabled, and having a guaranteed seat where I need it to be is a wonderful help. Staff is also friendly and helpful as well.

Always enjoy my movies here. Did try the extra comfy theater- well worth the upgrade cost. Have not seen IMAX, so I can't vouch for that, but regular theaters are great. Clean theater, reasonably comfortable seats and quality sound and picture.

We drove 52 minutes to see a movie that is not showing in our town.  Arctic was as good as expected.  Theater was cold and even with the blankets we always bring along we froze through the movie. Bathrooms were not clean and smelled bad.

Raising evaluations to 3 stars.  They responded to my feedback and I appreciate their letter.
It's a nice theatre, like most. But the other theatre in town let's you butter your own popcorn and make your own soda, which I like to do. But to watch a movie, you can't go wrong here.

Great theater.  Join their frequent movie goer club FMG for discounts on tickets and concessions.  Comfortable seats.  Imax!  Usually plenty of staff during peak hours to move you through lines quick.  Ample parking. Comfortable seats.
Great venue for unique plays with top notch performers. Also incredibly affordable. Not necessarily kid friendly.
We are so lucky to have such a fabulous resource in our city!
This historic venue provides high quality performances of contemporary and classic relevant theater. One of the best regional theaters anywhere.

Love this theater. It's small, but every show is different and they really use the space creativity. Tickets are very reasonably priced. 

Make sure you bring cash!

Reservations can be made over the phone or online.  They over cookies and coffee at intermission and before the shows!
Great venue with quality production
Beautiful, acoustically balanced space which makes any seat in the house enjoyable. Sound was very well balanced. Looking forward to attending additional events here in the future.

My wife and I took a nice date night to go see the nutcracker.  The performance was wonderful to say the least.

The seating and the view we had were great.  We didn't have enough time in intermission to order anything, but maybe that's because we are just slow haha.
Nice atmosphere. Great place for some evening entertainment. Came here with the wife and kids for a show about sleeping. Very Enjoyable.
Truly amazing concert hall. I performed here twice- both for the all Illinois junior band. Acoustics are perfect and seating is plenty
Beautiful venue for all the arts. Come to the Cafe during lunch for great food during the week

Love this place! I ordered a mini burrito - which I do every time - can't go wrong. The food is always good. Same cook for the last 8-9 years. You have to love continuity. Will  always go back to La Bambas to eat.
Food was good but it was a little pricey for what you get.
Love their food! Always good. The owners are super people!
We love this place good fast authentic Mexican food.
Very good even after years of being out of state.
A favorite to visit in the summers when visiting Champaign. Love their lemon custard. Their cold fudge is pretty great too.

Great local ice cream and custard! They are known for the lemon custard which I would highly recommend! It can get busy but they have a very nice drive through if you are on the go. If not you can sit outside and enjoy your icecream!
Always love the ice cream here. Staff was friendly and it smelled like fresh waffle cones. Tons of flavor, a must eat.
Nice ice cream! Sitting outside on their chairs is fantastic when the weather is good.

Delicious. I like to get custard with cold fudge but everything they have seems to be good. Rumor is that Tom Hanks likes to frequent Jarling's when he visits his brother who's a professor at the University. Don't be intimidated if there is a line, it moves very quickly. There's also a drive thru if you don't want to get out of your car. If you do want to eat at the restaurant, they have some seats inside as well as some picnic tables outside.
Awesome and plentiful, as always!! I was introduced to Golden Wok in 2004- and we are still enjoying the SAME dishes! I recommend this restaurant all the time.
Definitely not like home but the people are like home. I can also what I like here cooked the right way. Need to clean a little better.
It was good food but, a little pricy for dinner. I liked the Shrimp and Pepper Steak mixed with white rice.
Pretty good pad thai, quick, and a decent portion for what you pay.

I asked for spicey and I got spicey! This perfect little place gave me everything I asked for and more. I’ll never go anywhere else. Golden wok came through when most other Chinese restaurants were a let down. The staff was so friendly and also had a great sense of humor. I think I’ve finally found my go to place.
Fresh, healthy, delicious food and my go-to for lunch. Haven for a vegetarian! Try 201 & 202 daily specials. This is a unique restaurant that offers a perfect break from the craziness of life.
Real simple food. No fancy stuff, no oil and heavy spices. Just really healthy food.

I had the 202 Lunch Deal with Veggies. It tasted great and only costed 7$.
Ambiente could be better and the perso behind the counter could have put on a smile, but overall I was very statisfied. Great place for students to grab a balanced meal, especially vegans.

There is a hard working, talented and compassionate human being making wonderful food here. It is simple, not over-priced, honest and fresh, made from scratch, original recipes. I’ve been going to this restaurant for 10+ years and I am still caught by surprise with new dishes that reflect Hamid’s lifelong learning of cooking. He aces the meat and vegetarian option. And, in case you were wondering, yes, the man behind the counter is called Hamid!

Definitely one of the best place to eat in Champaign-Urbana. Jerusalem serves middle-eastern food, essentially Lebanese.
Healthy and inexpensive from meat, salad, sandwich, falafel, hummus to vegetarian dishes. Lamb shank is excellent. Best Baklava! Highly recommended.

Maize has great Mexican food, the prices are what you would expect, burritos are like 7 dollars here and tacos about 2. There's not much seating area but it's good enough to have one on one time with people here. They also serve great chips and salsa.
Such good food made so fast at an amazing price! If you are in the area you HAVE to check them out! Best Mexican food around!

I really don’t understand what makes this place so good. Average tacos at best. Average burritos. I’ve been here a few times and it’s just average all around. Compared to places around campus, there are better places but not many, but overall I’ve had much much better.
Amazing authentic Mexican food. Great service and affordable prices. I would have loved to have been able to bring a large group with me to eat, maybe in the not so distant future😉! Nice going.
Great food. Some of the best Mexican I’ve had outside of California. Not a taco truck by any means, but very good.
Good food. Big portions. A couple could share the peppered chicken which is great.  Expect to spend about $10 to $15 a person if not sharing. Nice employees.

The owner is a wonderful woman and the food is to die for. It's beyond Chinese takeout, this place is a legit fine dining Mandarin restaurant. Their red pepper chicken is my favorite Chinese dish ever!

One of my favorite restaurants in Champaign-Urbana. My family goes all the time, the owner knows us and starts our regular dishes as soon as we walk in. Spicy diced chicken, spicy fish in broth, stuffed tofu, and seafood in XO sauce. They have HUGE tables and a room in the back, great for big parties and the workers are always super nice. Highly recommend :)

Got food because we wanted Chinese and the place was close. Was pleasantly surprised that the food came quickly and tasted great! The lunch deal was a steal as well! Would recommend for anyone wanting to grab some Chinese!
I absolutely love coming to this place!  The food is awesome and the staff is wonderful!!  I come in at least once a week.
Comfortable place for casual dining. Good menu selection. Very nice staff. Good food.

Great service.  The two star review is because of the management's decision to offer a 10% discount on the kid's meal only and that amounted to $.50.  The hot bun was hard and stale and the french fries were burnt.  Our son could only eat about half of the hot dog and didn't eat any french fries.  The pizza was good and the waitress was great but management's SMALL discount on a kid's meal not eaten will keep us from going back.

We go every Sunday for half-priced pizza, great pizza for an awesome deal! Their homemade potato chips are tasty and the BBQ grilled cheese is delicious. The staff is really friendly and we feel at home every time we visit. Highly recommended!!
Absolutely amazing good and extremely curtious staff worth every single penny definetly recommend stopping in and grabbing a bite.

The portions were great. The meat & sides I ordered were very good. I got  the $13.00 Sampler. On the side I ordered MacNCheese, BBQ Beans, Potato Salad, and 6p Smoked Wings. The only thing I was sorta disappointed about was the $9- 6p that I purchase. I think it was very pricey for what you recieved. Possibly through a side in there & I could justify the price. 
As for the sauces, I'm not a fan but PLEASE don't let that stop you because I ate most of it without anything on them & it was SUPER DELICIOUS. This was my first time but definitely NOT my last. 
Too, I purchased a piece of double chocolate pie. I haven't eaten it yet but I'm sure it is as delicious as it looks. I can see why people are raving about it. 
One word of advice- Come hungry because the portions are actually filling.

loved this place, only in town for 2 days and ate there both nights.  every town needs a throw back like this.  great steak, salad bar and bread.  love the cast iron plates..sizzle sizzle. they were nice from the first phone for reservation to the service.

Service was absolutely phenomenal. Steak was average, a little chewy and not as tender as a ribeye should be. I feel like you can get better steaks in the area, I would be okay paying more for better quality. Prices here are reasonable. I would return, but this wouldn't be one of my first choices.

Service was great but not so much my steak. Ordered med. rare but steak was very thin with platter so hot that by the time I could cut and eat it, it was med. well. Salad bar excellent!!!! Best in town!!!

Very delicious.  Disappointed in service though.  It was our our 45th anniversary.  We mentioned it to server and he never offered a complimentary dessert.  When your bill is $200 it would have been nice to receive a small dessert.  It's all about the service and this was disappointing.

We walked in the front door at 5:10pm without a reservation.  We asked to sit in a booth for 2 people.  The host looked at the plan and asked us “Do you think you could be finished eating by 7?”  I got shocked by that horrendous question and my eyes got real big and surprised.  I have never been asked a rude question like that ever before. 

Good salad bar.  My husband was not satisfied with his steak.  I believe we were charged double on a few items on the bill.  
We will go to another steak house next time.

This place looks really run down. They allow you to build you own pizza, pasta, salad, etc. I got a pizza and my friend a pasta.

To start, the place doesn't look that clean. Ambience a little low. This place allows you to view you food being made, which was interesting. 

The pizza came out better that I would have anticipated looking at it made, but the pasta was atrocious. 

Overall, recommend the pizza, but do not come her for the pasta.
A favorite spot for tasty Italian food. The service here is attentive. The place has a great atmosphere. Menu is similar to a restaurant in El Paso I liked.

I SAID LIGHT DRESSING!!!!  And why did you have to put so much cheese on the salad???  We're you trying to make me fat??

I have eating issues, and I thought a nice and light salad from here would be fine, but the dressing was totally overused and there was just too much cheese.  The later is more my fault, but still.

I love the sandwiches though!!!

Very reasonably priced. We both had pizza, and it was decent. Great for students. I'd probably eat here again. The atmosphere is very casual, despite their site suggesting otherwise. You write your order on a piece of paper before handing it to the cashier. Fast service. 

Pepsi products for those that are curious.

I don't know why the reviews are so high for this place. The pizza tastes just a little better than frozen pizza. The crust tasted stale and brittle.  The atmosphere wasn't great either. it was a little chilly inside like they didn't have the heating on.

One of my favorite Indian restaurants, if you are looking for cheap good food, look no more! Very good meal for the price. My favorites are: 
Samosa
Deep fried leavened flour patties, stuffed with potatoes, green peas and spices 
Chicken Korma
Tender pieces of chicken cooked in curry cashew sauce (mild dish) 
Chicken Kabab Masala
Tender cubes of chicken sauteed in onions & tomatoes cooked in curry sauce (hot)

We love the food from Bombay Grill. Recently I was overcharged by a glitch on DoorDash. They called to let me know so I could get a refund. (DoorDash corrected the error for me.) I was grateful for that extra bit of care for they give for their customers.
My favorite Indian restaurant in town! The food is excellent, the prices are good, and the service is friendly and fast.
Very good food. Friendly atmosphere. Big portions.
Great service and delicious food!

As always, fabulously wonderful wine, meal and desserts. Service always excellent and friendly. So glad we were there Saturday evening. So sorry Milo's will be closing in late February. Always a place you can count on for lovely location and a relaxed quieter environment with friends and family for a hit the spot meal with that touch of elegance that's so comfortable.
Delicious food and excellent service. So sad they're closing soon. You should eat here before they close
Prompt friendly service. Nice selection of food. Had salads which were well prepared  and moderately priced. Substitutions were easy.

We were in for dinner on a Friday evening. Very casual atmosphere and we enjoyed the food. My only concern was the chicken pot pie, while delicious, could have been seasoned a bit more. This will be a restaurant we return too.
Gem of a restaurant in an out of the way location. Very unique and creative menu ideas which were very well executed. Service was also excellent.

My wife and I had the Taster's Menu. It was worth it, especially with the wine pairing option. Some courses, and wines, were better than others, but overall a great experience. Good atmosphere on our side of the restaurant; that it was not busy made it better. 
This restaurant is going out of business at the end of this month, Dec 31. Get there while you can!
Great food and wine selection. Wonderful staff, very accommodating and friendly. Atmosphere is classy but laid back.
Sad to see Bacaro close as it has great food.
WAND did a special report on closed restaurants in Champaign.

Great food and drinks,  fantastic wine dinners and Great wine list.  Staff is knowledgeable and very welcoming.  The pre fix menu always features great local and seasonal ingredients.  Presentation is impressive and interesting.  The dishes are all very well balanced and taste great!
Burgers are surprisingly good, and the physical set up is cool. Love the outdoor space.
Very fun. Great music and environment
Great burgers for half price on Friday!
Food was very underwhelming. Dry burgers with no seasoning. In my group there were about 6 burgers and nobody really liked them even during a BOGO deal.
Perfect for college students. Decently priced drinks with a dance / party atmosphere.

Fantastic service - a  quality cut you will not find at many places in Brisbane. These guys are pros at fades, with amazing clipper work and very handy with the scissors. First haircut I've walked out of genuinely impressed and received several compliments from the shop to home. If you're looking for a fresh chop, do yourself a favour and make an appointment. Cheers Jordan!
Had my hair dyed for the first time. Can't be happier than this. I feel 10 years younger! Kudos to talented and friendly Lorraine.

It's rare to come across a barber with such depth of knowledge. Jordan definitely knows how to cut hair according to different head shapes and with a diverse range skills. Cool dude too.

Would recommend! 👍👍
Jordan paid exceptional attention to detail and care. He explained everything perfectly and showed great technical skills. Highly recommend him to anyone wanting a quality cut.

If i could kiss Jordan and not be arrested i would. 
By far the best place in town for a haircut, shave or hair highlight. 
Have never once felt like i was being rushed out or that my requests were unreasonable.
Service is top notch.
Thanks Mark & Jordan for all the free laughs and always making me feel welcomed.

The food is GREAT especially the steak sandwich and crab Patty
My drink of choice would be the Margarita up. Not on the rocks.
I love the Brass Rail!! Good food.
Not pricey Been going there for about 40 yrs.

Great local place. Food is very good and they have a great bar. Service is very good and fast. They are open late too which is nice for a bite  to eat or for a drink. Very comfortable place. Ample parking.

The Brass Rail makes excellent Lehigh Valley-style cheesesteaks.  It’s an old-school type of restaurant.

Service is efficient and friendly.  

It’s casual and family-run. 

Highly recommended!
Love this place! Food is good, service is great and the prices are reasonable! What more could you ask for?

I have loved brass rail for many years. I am glad to see they have not really changed too much. I was disappointed though in their prices. I have always love their cheesesteak omelette. But the prices have steadily increased to the point i skip going there for breakfast. Its a shame because that was always a family tradition on sunday mornings but not anymore.
Wonderful time with Ayla and Melissa and class. Enjoyed making Ayla's Fascinators.
Pretty unique
Love this place. Cozy and relaxing with good coffee and snacks. To no fault of their own the parking sucks and I wish they were in a different location.

Nice, relaxing atmosphere. Coffee okay, tea good, plain espresso...less so. But the staff are friendly, the bathrooms are gender neutral, and they offer a variety of seating suitable both for socializing and working.
A quaint coffee shop with a small business vibe nestled just on the outskirts of campus. Parking is a nightmare. I recommend walking the beautiful UofI campus to get there instead of driving.
Great for studying! I wish they would actually make beverages extra hot though!
Cozy place, great for studying. Helpful staff and tasty food.

I love going to Pekara for a bright, happy place to grab breakfast and sit and work for a while. The quiches are my favorite, but the cinnamon roll is amazing (i think there's a hint of almond extract in it... Yum). I'm a tea drinker so I can't comment on the coffee, but I'm a big fan of the tea and can usually get a second cup out of it if I ask for more hot water.

This weekend, my best friend and I had brunch at Pekara. We were both impressed by the options on the menu, as well as everything displayed in the bakery. As first time customers, the woman who was serving us was so helpful and friendly in her recommendations. The cinnamon roll was *amazing*. Great people, great place, great food. We enjoyed the atmosphere of this downtown location as well. We are looking forward to repeating our business here!

Nothing special.  We have gone twice for desserts, since they call themselves a bakery, and were highly disappointed both times.  This time we got cupcakes that were so dry they should have been in the trash.  I have also heard they bake almost nothing themselves, I think they need a new distributor of baked goods....cupcakes should not be so dry and tasteless.  On a good note, the latte was delicious.

Great food, well-priced and a good variety of vegetarian flavors too.
One of the only European style cafes in town with a great atmosphere and friendly staff.

I like this cafe, however, this cafe closed at 6 pm, Friday. I was reading a book in the cafe today around 6 pm and one staff let me know that they are closing soon. The google information may need to update their hours.
